OL,3,GYorkshire & Humber
OL,4,
OL,5,CThis Evening and Tonight:FSunny spells
OL,6,Fcontinue through the evening, though
OL,7,Fit will feel cool in a northerly
OL,8,Fbreeze. Largely dry overnight, with
OL,9,Fclear spells developing, although a
OL,10,Ffew isolated coastal showers are
OL,11,Flikely. Turning chilly with a local
OL,12,Frural frost possible in places.
OL,13,
OL,14,CWednesday:FAfter a chilly start, sunny
OL,15,Fspells develop through the day.
OL,16,FLargely dry and cool, though
OL,17,Foccasional coastal showers remain
OL,18,Fpossible. Light winds, with a frosty
OL,19,Fnight to come.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
